{
    "word": "Pessimism",
    "definitions": [
        "The opinion or doctrine that everything in nature is ordered for or tends to the worst, or that the world is wholly evil; -- opposed to optimism.",
        "A disposition to take the least hopeful view of a situation."
    ],
    "examples": [
    ],
    "etymology": "[L. pessimus worst, superl. of pejor worse: cf. F. pessimisme. Cf. Impair.]"
